      <h2>Before you claim</h2>
<p>You can get a refund if you have a 7 Day or longer Travelcard or Bus &amp; Tram Pass.</p>
<p>We will ask you to send us details of your illness and when it started. This could be a:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Medical certificate</li>
    <li>Letter on headed paper from your doctor or employer</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>If your illness started less than 6 weeks ago</strong>, we'll refund you from the start of your illness.</p>
<p><strong>If your illness started more than 6 weeks ago</strong>, your refund will be calculated as 6 weeks from the date of your application.</p>
<p>If you want to claim a refund, you cannot use the ticket again. You will not get a refund if you use the ticket after claiming.</p>
<p>We charge a &pound;5 admin fee for this refund.</p>
<h2>Claim a refund</h2>
<p>Please <a href="/help-and-contact/contact-us-about-oyster">fill in the Oyster form</a>, and provide us with:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Details of your illness and when it started</li>
    <li>A medical certificate or letter on headed paper from your doctor or employer</li>
    <li>Your contact details (name, address and phone number)</li>
</ul>
      
           
      
      
        
          
        
      
    
